!!!
%html.no-js
  %head
    %meta{ charset: 'utf-8' }
    %meta{ content: 'IE=edge,chrome=1', http_equiv: 'X-UA-Compatible' }
    %meta{ content: 'width=device-width', name: 'viewport' }

    %title= current_page.data.title || ""

    = javascript_include_tag 'dependencies/modernizr'
    = stylesheet_link_tag 'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Roboto'
    = stylesheet_link_tag 'application'

  %body{ class: page_classes }

    #clock

    .info-icon
      ?

    .info-box
      The Autonomist is a self determining news feed gone wrong. Parsing current stories across the web at random, The Autonomist generates fictitious headlines. The results reflect a future in which content sorting algorithms, often utilized within social networks and news platforms, take on a life of their own.

    = yield

    = javascript_include_tag 'application'
